From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000011 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Jun 2026 18:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: OMAP4: steelhead: self-contained CPU1 bring-up auto-probe (debug)

Observability for the OMAP4460 HS silent SMP deadlock WITHOUT relying on the
(flaky) network. On a maxcpus=1 boot a late_initcall kthread waits ~30 s for the
HDMI framebuffer console to come up, then onlines CPU1 (add_cpu(1)). Combined
with the instrumentation patch, the STEELHEAD-SMP milestones print synchronously
to the screen, so the last line before a freeze pinpoints exactly where CPU1
bring-up dies; on success nr_online jumps to 2. Pair with cmdline
systemd.unit=multi-user.target so the desktop compositor does not own HDMI.

NOT for release -- debug probe, drop once CPU1 bring-up works.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap-smp.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap-smp.c
@@ -15,6 +15,9 @@
 #include <linux/init.h>
 #include <linux/device.h>
 #include <linux/smp.h>
+#include <linux/cpu.h>
+#include <linux/kthread.h>
+#include <linux/delay.h>
 #include <linux/io.h>
 #include <linux/irqchip/arm-gic.h>
 
@@ -426,6 +429,33 @@
 	dsb_sev();
 }
 
+/*
+ * Steelhead DEBUG (drop before release): self-contained CPU1 bring-up probe.
+ * On a maxcpus=1 boot, ~30 s after init (once the HDMI fb console is up), online
+ * CPU1 from a kthread so the patch-0009 milestones print to the screen with NO
+ * network needed. The last STEELHEAD-SMP line before a freeze pinpoints where
+ * CPU1 bring-up dies; if it succeeds, nr_online jumps to 2.
+ */
+static int steelhead_smp_probe(void *unused)
+{
+	int rc;
+
+	ssleep(30);
+	pr_emerg("STEELHEAD-SMP: ===== AUTO-PROBE: onlining CPU1 now (nr_online=%d) =====\n",
+		 num_online_cpus());
+	rc = add_cpu(1);
+	pr_emerg("STEELHEAD-SMP: ===== AUTO-PROBE: add_cpu(1) rc=%d nr_online=%d =====\n",
+		 rc, num_online_cpus());
+	return 0;
+}
+
+static int __init steelhead_smp_probe_init(void)
+{
+	kthread_run(steelhead_smp_probe, NULL, "steelhead-smp-probe");
+	return 0;
+}
+late_initcall(steelhead_smp_probe_init);
+
 const struct smp_operations omap4_smp_ops __initconst = {
 	.smp_init_cpus		= omap4_smp_init_cpus,
 	.smp_prepare_cpus	= omap4_smp_prepare_cpus,
